  {
    q: "Which Groen kettle models do you service?",
    a: "Full Groen steam-jacketed kettle line. TDB-40, TDB-60, TDB-80, TDB-100 gas-fired models (gallon capacities). AH-1E electric tilt kettles. INA series direct-steam. ABC series braising pans (tilt skillets used as combination cooking surfaces). Plus the older Groen K-series and the Crown Steam line under the Ali Group umbrella where applicable.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Groen and Cleveland Range kettles?",
    a: "Both are American-made steam-jacketed kettle specialists. Cleveland Range is older (1932 founding) and is in the Welbilt portfolio (Ali Group at the ultimate parent level). Groen is younger (1947 founding) and was acquired directly into Ali Group around 2001. Both produce comparable build quality and similar capacity ranges. Service tree is similar across both brands: thermopile, gas valve, heating element, pressure relief valve, sight glass, mixer drive (where applicable). We service both with no preference; parts availability is good for both through Ali Group's distribution network.",
  },
  {
    q: "What fails most often on Groen kettles?",
    a: "On gas-fired TDB units the leading service items are thermopile (year 4-7, $260-440), gas valve (year 8-12, $480-720), pressure relief valve (annual safety inspection, replace as needed $280-440), water-level sight glass cleaning, and pilot orifice service. On electric AH-1E tilt kettles: heating element (year 6-10, $640-920), tilt motor service, contactor relay (year 7-9, $340-540). On ABC braising pans: tilt mechanism service, gas burner service on gas variants, electric element on electric variants.",
  },
  {
    q: "What does Groen kettle repair cost?",
    a: "$120 commercial diagnostic, applied to repair. Most Groen kettle repairs run $260-820 all-in. Thermopile $260-440. Gas valve $480-720. Heating element on electric AH-1E $640-920. Pressure relief valve $280-440. Tilt mechanism service $340-540. Mixer drive on combination units $480-820. We quote in writing before any parts are ordered.",
  },
  {
    q: "Are Groen parts hard to source?",
    a: "No. Ali Group parts network has strong North American distribution with 3-7 day standard ship on common service items. Common parts (thermopiles, gas valves, heating elements, pressure relief valves, tilt motors) we carry on the van for the major TDB and AH-1E model sizes. Specialty parts are dealer-order with typical 5-10 day ship through Ali Group's authorized service network.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. Groen component warranties (where applicable) are processed separately through Ali Group's authorized service network. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410, BBB A+ accredited.",
  },
];

