</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Groen in the SoCal commercial steam market</p>
    <h2>The Ali Group steam equipment specialty since 1947.</h2>

    <p>Groen is the American commercial steam equipment manufacturer founded in 1947 in Illinois. Ali Group acquired Groen around 2001. Sister brands within Ali Group include Beverage-Air, Scotsman, Ice-O-Matic, Champion (commercial dishwashers), and approximately 25 other foodservice equipment brands. Cleveland Range (the other major American steam-jacketed kettle brand) joined the Ali Group corporate family via Welbilt's 2022 acquisition, making Groen and Cleveland Range corporate siblings at the Ali Group level despite competing in similar product categories.</p>

    <p>Across SoCal, Groen TDB tilt kettles are common in institutional kitchens (LAUSD, UC and CSU dining services, hospital cafeterias), large catering operations, banquet kitchens, and high-volume restaurant operations producing soup, stew, sauce, or stock. The TDB-40 and TDB-60 are the most common in our service calls. Electric AH-1E tilt kettles appear in urban kitchens with limited gas service. ABC braising pans serve dual-purpose cooking surfaces in operations that need both kettle and large-format sauteing capacity.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, applied to repair. Same-day response across LA, OC, Ventura. Next-day for Riverside and San Bernardino. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/kettle-repair/">commercial kettle repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Groen product lines we service</p>
    <h2>Series and common service items.</h2>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">TDB Series, Gas-Fired Tilt Kettles</h3>
    <p>TDB-40, TDB-60, TDB-80, TDB-100 (gallon capacity). Self-contained gas-fired steam jacket with manual or motorized tilt for emptying. Standing pilot or electronic ignition fires the burner heating jacket water; pressure rises to 15-50 psig depending on model. Common service items: thermopile (year 4-7), gas valve (year 8-12), pressure relief valve (annual safety inspection), water-level sight glass cleaning, tilt mechanism service.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">AH-1E Series, Electric Tilt Kettles</h3>
    <p>Electric heating element heats jacket water rather than gas burner. AH-1E-30 and AH-1E-40 are the common sizes. Service items: heating element (year 6-10), contactor or relay failure, pressure relief valve, jacket water-level control, tilt motor service.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">INA Series, Direct-Steam</h3>
    <p>Direct-steam kettles connect to a central building boiler rather than self-generating steam. Used in larger institutional kitchens with central boiler systems. Service includes the kettle architecture plus the steam supply valve, condensate trap, and jacket inlet/outlet fittings.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">ABC Series Braising Pans</h3>
    <p>Tilt skillets / braising pans serve as dual-purpose cooking surfaces (kettle-style boiling plus large-format sauteing). Gas and electric variants. Service items: gas burner service on gas variants, electric element on electric variants, tilt mechanism, drain assembly.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Real Groen repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>UCLA campus dining, Groen TDB-60 (year 9)</h3>
        <p>Pilot wouldn't stay lit before lunch service. Diagnosed thermopile failure: millivolt 170 mV (needs 250+). Replaced thermopile with OEM Groen part. Tested pilot through full burner cycle. Total: $120 plus $340 part plus 75 minutes labor = $560.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills hotel banquet kitchen, Groen TDB-80 (year 11)</h3>
        <p>Pressure relief valve weeping during annual safety inspection. Replaced relief valve, provided inspection documentation appropriate for hotel mechanical maintenance file. Total: $120 plus $360 part plus 50 minutes labor = $545.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>OC catering kitchen, Groen AH-1E-40 electric (year 8)</h3>
        <p>Kettle not heating, jacket water cold. Element continuity test: open circuit on heating element. Replaced element. Tested under load 45 minutes, jacket pressure recovery normal. Total: $120 plus $720 part plus 90 minutes labor = $980.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Cedars-Sinai cafeteria, Groen ABC-30 braising pan (year 12)</h3>
        <p>Tilt mechanism stiff and binding. Disassembled tilt drive, cleaned old grease, replaced worn bushings, re-greased and tested. Tilt cycle smooth through full range. Total: $120 plus $260 parts plus 90 minutes labor = $470.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

